Debian Package Building Instructions
====================================

This directory contains the Debian packaging files for OLLMchat.

Packaging modes
---------------

Two layouts are maintained:

### Monolithic (default)

Builds all-in-one `.deb` packages for GitHub release downloads until an apt
repository is available. Two variants are published:

| Package | Script | `local_gguf` | Use when |
|---------|--------|--------------|----------|
| **ollmchat** | `use-monolithic-package.sh` (default) | `enabled` | Local GGUF via libllama plus remote backends |
| **ollmchat-remote-only** | `use-monolithic-remote-only-package.sh` | `disabled` | Ollama / OpenAI-compatible APIs only |

The active variant is selected by the switch script, which copies the
matching `control` and `.install` files and writes `debian/local-gguf`
(`enabled` or `disabled`). `debian/rules` passes that to Meson as
`-Dlocal_gguf=…`.

A normal Meson build (outside Debian) uses `-Dlocal_gguf=auto` by default
and includes libllama when it is found on the build host.

**ollmchat** (with libllama):

```bash
./debian/use-monolithic-package.sh   # already the default in git
# libllama-dev required; see scripts/fetch-libllama.sh on older distros
dpkg-buildpackage -us -uc -b
```

**ollmchat-remote-only**:

```bash
./debian/use-monolithic-remote-only-package.sh
dpkg-buildpackage -us -uc -b
./debian/use-monolithic-package.sh   # switch back when done
```

Build both release packages (clean rebuild between variants):

```bash
./debian/use-monolithic-package.sh
./scripts/fetch-libllama.sh   # if libllama-dev is not in apt
dpkg-buildpackage -us -uc -b
rm -rf build
./debian/use-monolithic-remote-only-package.sh
dpkg-buildpackage -us -uc -b
./debian/use-monolithic-package.sh
```

`ollmchat` and `ollmchat-remote-only` conflict; only one may be installed
at a time. Both install the same `/usr/bin/ollmchat` application.

GitHub release AppImages and the Windows installer use the same **remote-only**
build (no libllama): `OLLMchat-remote-only-*.AppImage` and
`OLLMchat-remote-only-Setup.exe`. See `docs/creating-releases.md`.

### Split packages (for apt repository)

Builds separate runtime, -dev, tools, and doc packages. Switch to this
when publishing to an apt repository.

```bash
./debian/use-split-packages.sh
dpkg-buildpackage -us -uc -b
./debian/use-monolithic-package.sh   # switch back when done
```

Canonical definitions live in `debian/monolithic/`, `debian/monolithic-remote-only/`,
and `debian/split/`. The switch scripts copy the chosen layout into the active
`debian/` files.

Split package layout
--------------------

When using split packages, the source builds:

### Core / data libraries
1. **libocsqlite1** / **libocsqlite-dev** — SQLite helpers (libocsqlite.so)
2. **libocfiles1** / **libocfiles-dev** — File and project management (libocfiles.so)
3. **libocrpc1** / **libocrpc-dev** — JSON-RPC wire types (libocrpc.so)
4. **libollamaweb1** / **libollamaweb-dev** — Ollama HTTP client (libollamaweb.so)

### Markdown libraries
5. **libocmarkdown1** / **libocmarkdown-dev** — Markdown parsing (libocmarkdown.so)
6. **libocmarkdowngtk1** / **libocmarkdowngtk-dev** — GTK markdown rendering (libocmarkdowngtk.so)

### LLM stack libraries
7. **libollmchat1** / **libollmchat-dev** — LLM API access (libollmchat.so)
8. **libollmchatgtk1** / **libollmchatgtk-dev** — GTK chat widgets (libollmchatgtk.so)
9. **liboctools1** / **liboctools-dev** — LLM tool implementations (liboctools.so)
10. **libocvector1** / **libocvector-dev** — Vector search (libocvector.so)
11. **liboccoder1** / **liboccoder-dev** — Code editor / agent UI (liboccoder.so)
12. **libocmcp1** / **libocmcp-dev** — MCP integration (libocmcp.so)

### Application and tools
13. **ollmchat** — Main application and ollmfilesd daemon
14. **ollmchat-tools** — Command-line tools (oc-md2html, oc-html2md)
15. **ollmchat-doc** — Test executables and documentation

Building packages
-----------------

1. Install build dependencies:
   ```bash
   sudo apt-get install build-essential devscripts debhelper meson ninja-build \
     pkg-config valac libgee-0.8-dev libglib2.0-dev libjson-glib-dev \
     libsoup-3.0-dev libxml2-dev libsqlite3-dev \
     libgtk-4-dev libgtksourceview-5-dev libadwaita-1-dev gobject-introspection \
     libgirepository1.0-dev libtree-sitter-dev libseccomp-dev libgit2-glib-1.0-dev \
     libopenblas-dev liblapack-dev libfaiss-dev
   ```

2. Build the packages:
   ```bash
   dpkg-buildpackage -us -uc -b
   ```

3. The resulting .deb files will be in the parent directory.

Install locations
-----------------

- Libraries: /usr/lib/
- Headers: /usr/include/
- VAPI files: /usr/share/vala/vapi/
- GIR files: /usr/share/gir-1.0/
- Typelib files: /usr/lib/*/girepository-1.0/
- Application: /usr/bin/ (ollmchat)
- Tools: /usr/bin/ (oc-md2html, oc-html2md)
- Test executables: /usr/share/doc/ollmchat/ (oc-test-*, split mode only)
